articles.title: DECEMBER 1975
articles.summary: This December 1975 bulletin for an astronomy club details recent activities, including a sparsely attended star party at Henry Coe State Park and a well-attended general meeting featuring member equipment displays. Upcoming events include a general meeting with talks on Saturn and stellar coordinate charts, a star party, and a board meeting, along with a critical announcement about the non-renewal of the Mt. Umanhum observatory lease. The document also provides astronomical data for December, such as Great Red Spot transit times and occultation predictions.
